<resources>

    <!-- **Naming convention followed for id in explore-india**
            <what>_<where>_<description>

            where <what> is the layout name
                  <where> is the abbreviation of the views
                  <description> is the unique name for the id

            eg; login_et_name

            To use the id in java. Just do android:id=@id/login_et_name

             Abbreviations :

               EditText = et
               TextView = tv
               Button = btn
               Menu = menu
               ListView = lv
               RecyclerView = rv
               CardView = cv
               ImageView = img
               LinearLayout = ll
               ConstrantLayout = cl
               RelativeLayout = rl
               ProgressBar - pb
               Checkbox - chk
               RadioButton - rb
               ToggleButton - tb
               Spinner - spn
               ViewPager = vp
               Toolbar = tb
               SearchView = sv

               If new ids are needed to be created apart from the id's mentioned here,
                please use the above convention.

               This ids are created in accordance with final UI mocks. Refer the UI mock.-->

